usdL2fMIB.name: usdL2fMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

usdL2fMIB.contactinfo: Unisphere Networks, Inc. Postal: 10 Technology Park Drive Westford, MA 01886 USA Tel: +1 978 589 5800 Email: mib@UnisphereNetworks.com
usdL2fMIB.description: The Layer 2 Forwarding MIB for the Unisphere Networks enterprise.

UsdL2fTunnelId.name: UsdL2fTunnelId
UsdL2fTunnelId.description: An L2F Tunnel ID. Implementation constraints may restrict the range of values actually used.

UsdL2fSessionId.name: UsdL2fSessionId
UsdL2fSessionId.description: An L2F Session ID. Implementation constraints may restrict the range of values actually used.

UsdL2fAdminState.name: UsdL2fAdminState
UsdL2fAdminState.description: The administrative state exerted on L2F tunnels sessions at some scope of control. enabled New tunnels/sessions may be instantiated. disabled All tunnels/sessions are terminated. drain No new tunnels/sessions may be instantiated, but any existing tunnels/sessions may persist until they expire by other means. The DESCRIPTION clause of an object defined to have this syntax must describe the scope of control that object exerts (e.g., all tunnels/sessions across the system, sessions within a single tunnel, etc.).

UsdL2fTransport.name: UsdL2fTransport
UsdL2fTransport.description: Transport type over which L2F is carried.

usdL2fSysConfigAdminState.name: usdL2fSysConfigAdminState
usdL2fSysConfigAdminState.description: Exerts control over all L2F tunnels/sessions in the system.

usdL2fSysConfigDestructTimeout.name: usdL2fSysConfigDestructTimeout
usdL2fSysConfigDestructTimeout.description: The amount of time, in seconds, to preserve dynamic tunnels/sessions after they become inactive, e.g. to poll their statistics.

usdL2fSysConfigIpChecksumEnable.name: usdL2fSysConfigIpChecksumEnable
usdL2fSysConfigIpChecksumEnable.description: Enable/disable IP checksumming for tunnels with UDP/IP transport.

usdL2fSysConfigReceiveDataSequencingIgno.name: usdL2fSysConfigReceiveDataSequencingIgnore
usdL2fSysConfigReceiveDataSequencingIgno.description: Enable/disable ignoring of receive sequencing of L2F data packets.

usdL2fSysStatusProtocolVersion.name: usdL2fSysStatusProtocolVersion
usdL2fSysStatusProtocolVersion.description: Vector of supported L2F protocol version and revision numbers. Supported versions are identified via a two octet pairing where the first octet indicates the version and the second octet contains the revision.

usdL2fSysStatusVendorName.name: usdL2fSysStatusVendorName
usdL2fSysStatusVendorName.description: Vendor name of the L2F protocol stack.

usdL2fSysStatusFirmwareRev.name: usdL2fSysStatusFirmwareRev
usdL2fSysStatusFirmwareRev.description: Firmware revision for the L2F protocol stack.

usdL2fSysStatusFailedDestinations.name: usdL2fSysStatusFailedDestinations
usdL2fSysStatusFailedDestinations.description: Number of destination creation attempts that failed.

usdL2fSysStatusActiveDestinations.name: usdL2fSysStatusActiveDestinations
usdL2fSysStatusActiveDestinations.description: Number of destinations having at least one active tunnel.

usdL2fSysStatusFailedTunnels.name: usdL2fSysStatusFailedTunnels
usdL2fSysStatusFailedTunnels.description: Number of tunnel creation attempts that failed to reach the established state.

usdL2fSysStatusFailedTunnelAuthens.name: usdL2fSysStatusFailedTunnelAuthens
usdL2fSysStatusFailedTunnelAuthens.description: Number of tunnel creation attempts that failed authentication.

usdL2fSysStatusFailedSessions.name: usdL2fSysStatusFailedSessions
usdL2fSysStatusFailedSessions.description: Number of session creation attempts that failed to reach the established state.

usdL2fDestConfigTable.name: usdL2fDestConfigTable
usdL2fDestConfigTable.description: The L2F destination configuration table. Each entry in this table has a corresponding entry in the Interfaces MIB ifTable, and in usdL2fDestStatsTable.

usdL2fDestConfigEntry.name: usdL2fDestConfigEntry
usdL2fDestConfigEntry.description: Describes the configuration attributes of an L2F destination.

usdL2fDestConfigIfIndex.description: Same value as ifIndex for the corresponding entry in Interfaces MIB ifTable.

usdL2fDestConfigRowStatus.name: usdL2fDestConfigRowStatus
usdL2fDestConfigRowStatus.description: An implementation may choose not to support administrative configuration of tunnels.

usdL2fDestStatusTable.name: usdL2fDestStatusTable
usdL2fDestStatusTable.description: The L2F destination status table. Each entry in this table has a corresponding entry in the Interfaces MIB ifTable, and in usdL2fDestConfigTable.

usdL2fDestStatusEntry.name: usdL2fDestStatusEntry
usdL2fDestStatusEntry.description: Describes the status attributes of an L2F destination.

usdL2fDestStatusTransport.name: usdL2fDestStatusTransport

usdL2fDestStatusEffectiveAdminState.name: usdL2fDestStatusEffectiveAdminState
usdL2fDestStatusEffectiveAdminState.description: The administrative state currently in effect. This could be the configured admin state for this destination, or an overriding admin state exerted from a higher hierarchical level (system).

usdL2fDestStatusFailedTunnels.name: usdL2fDestStatusFailedTunnels

usdL2fDestStatusFailedTunnelAuthens.name: usdL2fDestStatusFailedTunnelAuthens
usdL2fDestStatusFailedTunnelAuthens.description: Number of tunnel creation attempts that failed authentication.

usdL2fDestStatusFailedSessions.name: usdL2fDestStatusFailedSessions
usdL2fDestStatusFailedSessions.description: Number of session creation attempts that failed to reach the established state.

usdL2fDestStatTable.description: The L2F destination statistics table. Describes the aggregate control and payload statistics for all L2F tunnels configured on each destination. Each entry in this table has a corresponding entry in the Interfaces MIB ifTable, and in usdL2fDestConfigTable.

usdL2fDestStatEntry.description: Describes the aggregate L2F control and payload statistics for all L2F tunnels on an L2F destination.

usdL2fDestStatIfIndex.name: usdL2fDestStatIfIndex
usdL2fDestStatIfIndex.description: Same value as ifIndex for the corresponding entry in Interfaces MIB ifTable.

usdL2fDestStatCtlRecvErrors.name: usdL2fDestStatCtlRecvErrors
usdL2fDestStatCtlRecvErrors.description: Number of control packets incurring reception errors.

usdL2fDestStatCtlRecvDiscards.name: usdL2fDestStatCtlRecvDiscards
usdL2fDestStatCtlRecvDiscards.description: Number of control packets discarded after reception.

usdL2fDestStatCtlSendErrors.name: usdL2fDestStatCtlSendErrors
usdL2fDestStatCtlSendErrors.description: Number of control packets incurring transmission errors.

usdL2fDestStatCtlSendDiscards.name: usdL2fDestStatCtlSendDiscards
usdL2fDestStatCtlSendDiscards.description: Number of control packets discarded before transmission.

usdL2fDestStatPayRecvErrors.name: usdL2fDestStatPayRecvErrors
usdL2fDestStatPayRecvErrors.description: Number of payload packets incurring reception errors.

usdL2fDestStatPayRecvDiscards.name: usdL2fDestStatPayRecvDiscards
usdL2fDestStatPayRecvDiscards.description: Number of payload packets discarded after reception.

usdL2fDestStatPaySendErrors.name: usdL2fDestStatPaySendErrors
usdL2fDestStatPaySendErrors.description: Number of payload packets incurring transmission errors.

usdL2fDestStatPaySendDiscards.name: usdL2fDestStatPaySendDiscards
usdL2fDestStatPaySendDiscards.description: Number of payload packets discarded before transmission.

usdL2fTunnelConfigTable.name: usdL2fTunnelConfigTable
usdL2fTunnelConfigTable.description: The L2F tunnel configuration table. Each entry in this table has a corresponding entry in the Interfaces MIB ifTable, and in usdL2fTunnelStatsTable.

usdL2fTunnelConfigEntry.name: usdL2fTunnelConfigEntry
usdL2fTunnelConfigEntry.description: Describes the configuration attributes of an L2F tunnel.

usdL2fTunnelConfigIfIndex.name: usdL2fTunnelConfigIfIndex
usdL2fTunnelConfigIfIndex.description: Same value as ifIndex for the corresponding entry in Interfaces MIB ifTable.

usdL2fTunnelConfigRowStatus.name: usdL2fTunnelConfigRowStatus
usdL2fTunnelConfigRowStatus.description: An implementation may choose not to support administrative configuration of tunnels.

usdL2fTunnelStatusTable.name: usdL2fTunnelStatusTable
usdL2fTunnelStatusTable.description: The L2F tunnel status and statistics table. Each entry in this table has a corresponding entry in the Interfaces MIB ifTable, and in usdL2fTunnelConfigTable.

usdL2fTunnelStatusEntry.name: usdL2fTunnelStatusEntry
usdL2fTunnelStatusEntry.description: An L2F tunnel interface stats entry.

usdL2fTunnelStatusIfIndex.name: usdL2fTunnelStatusIfIndex
usdL2fTunnelStatusIfIndex.description: Same as the value of ifIndex for the corresponding entry in Interfaces MIB ifTable.

usdL2fTunnelStatusTransport.name: usdL2fTunnelStatusTransport
usdL2fTunnelStatusTransport.description: The underlying transport over which this L2F tunnel is carried.

usdL2fTunnelStatusEffectiveAdminState.name: usdL2fTunnelStatusEffectiveAdminState
usdL2fTunnelStatusEffectiveAdminState.description: The administrative state currently in effect. This could be the configured admin state for this tunnel, or an overriding admin state exerted from a higher hierarchical level (system, destination).

usdL2fTunnelStatusState.name: usdL2fTunnelStatusState
usdL2fTunnelStatusState.description: The current state of the tunnel.

usdL2fTunnelStatusInitiated.name: usdL2fTunnelStatusInitiated
usdL2fTunnelStatusInitiated.description: Indicates whether the tunnel was initiated locally, or by the remote tunnel peer.

usdL2fTunnelStatusRemoteHostName.name: usdL2fTunnelStatusRemoteHostName
usdL2fTunnelStatusRemoteHostName.description: The host name obtained during the tunnel establishment phase (via the Host Name AVP) of the L2F peer. If the tunnel is idle, this object should maintain its value from the last time it was connected, or a zero-length string if no name was previously known.

usdL2fTunnelStatusTotalSessions.name: usdL2fTunnelStatusTotalSessions
usdL2fTunnelStatusTotalSessions.description: The total number of sessions that this tunnel has successfully connected through to its tunnel peer since this tunnel was created, including those that have since terminated.

usdL2fTunnelStatusFailedSessions.name: usdL2fTunnelStatusFailedSessions
usdL2fTunnelStatusFailedSessions.description: The number of sessions that were initiated but failed to reach the established phase.

usdL2fTunnelStatusActiveSessions.name: usdL2fTunnelStatusActiveSessions
usdL2fTunnelStatusActiveSessions.description: The current number of sessions in the established state.

usdL2fTunnelStatusLastErrorCode.name: usdL2fTunnelStatusLastErrorCode
usdL2fTunnelStatusLastErrorCode.description: The last value of the error code as described in the Result Code AVP which caused the tunnel to disconnect.

usdL2fTunnelStatusLastErrorMessage.name: usdL2fTunnelStatusLastErrorMessage
usdL2fTunnelStatusLastErrorMessage.description: The last value of the optional message as described in the Result Code AVP which caused the tunnel to disconnect.

usdL2fTunnelStatusCumEstabTime.name: usdL2fTunnelStatusCumEstabTime
usdL2fTunnelStatusCumEstabTime.description: The cumulative time in seconds that this tunnel, since first being created, has spent in the established state (which may be punctuated by intervals outside the established state).

usdL2fTunnelStatEntry.name: usdL2fTunnelStatEntry
usdL2fTunnelStatEntry.description: Describes the L2F control and payload statistics for an L2F tunnel.

usdL2fTunnelStatIfIndex.name: usdL2fTunnelStatIfIndex
usdL2fTunnelStatIfIndex.description: Same value as ifIndex for the corresponding entry in Interfaces MIB ifTable.

usdL2fTunnelStatCtlRecvErrors.name: usdL2fTunnelStatCtlRecvErrors
usdL2fTunnelStatCtlRecvErrors.description: Number of control packets incurring reception errors.

usdL2fTunnelStatCtlRecvDiscards.name: usdL2fTunnelStatCtlRecvDiscards

usdL2fTunnelStatCtlSendErrors.name: usdL2fTunnelStatCtlSendErrors
usdL2fTunnelStatCtlSendErrors.description: Number of control packets incurring transmission errors.

usdL2fTunnelStatCtlSendDiscards.description: Number of control packets discarded before transmission.

usdL2fTunnelStatPayRecvErrors.name: usdL2fTunnelStatPayRecvErrors
usdL2fTunnelStatPayRecvErrors.description: Number of payload packets incurring reception errors.

usdL2fTunnelStatPayRecvDiscards.description: Number of payload packets discarded after reception.

usdL2fTunnelStatPaySendErrors.description: Number of payload packets incurring transmission errors.

usdL2fTunnelStatPaySendDiscards.name: usdL2fTunnelStatPaySendDiscards
usdL2fTunnelStatPaySendDiscards.description: Number of payload packets discarded before transmission.

usdL2fTunnelStatCtlRecvOutOfSequence.name: usdL2fTunnelStatCtlRecvOutOfSequence
usdL2fTunnelStatCtlRecvOutOfSequence.description: Number of control packets not received in the correct sequence number order.

usdL2fMapTifSidToSifEntry.name: usdL2fMapTifSidToSifEntry
usdL2fMapTifSidToSifEntry.description: A mapping of TunnelIf/SessionId to SessionIf.

usdL2fMapTifSidToSifLocalSessionId.name: usdL2fMapTifSidToSifLocalSessionId
usdL2fMapTifSidToSifLocalSessionId.description: A local session ID on the associated tunnel interface.

usdL2fMapTifSidToSifSessionIfIndex.name: usdL2fMapTifSidToSifSessionIfIndex
usdL2fMapTifSidToSifSessionIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the session interface identified by this entry's Tunnel ifIndex and local Session Id pair.

usdL2fMapTidToTifTable.name: usdL2fMapTidToTifTable
usdL2fMapTidToTifTable.description: Map L2F tunnel IDs to tunnel interfaces.

usdL2fMapTidToTifEntry.description: A mapping of L2F tunnel ID to tunnel interface.

usdL2fMapTidToTifIfIndex.name: usdL2fMapTidToTifIfIndex
usdL2fMapTidToTifIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the tunnel interface having the associated tunnel identifier.

usdL2fSessionConfigTable.name: usdL2fSessionConfigTable
usdL2fSessionConfigTable.description: The L2F session configuration table. Each entry in this table has a corresponding entry in the Interfaces MIB ifTable, and in usdL2fSessionStatsTable.

usdL2fSessionConfigEntry.name: usdL2fSessionConfigEntry
usdL2fSessionConfigEntry.description: Describes the configuration attributes of an L2F session.

usdL2fSessionConfigIfIndex.name: usdL2fSessionConfigIfIndex
usdL2fSessionConfigIfIndex.description: Same value as ifIndex for the corresponding entry in Interfaces MIB ifTable.

usdL2fSessionConfigRowStatus.name: usdL2fSessionConfigRowStatus
usdL2fSessionConfigRowStatus.description: An implementation may choose not to support administrative configuration of tunnels.

usdL2fSessionStatusTable.name: usdL2fSessionStatusTable
usdL2fSessionStatusTable.description: The L2F session status and statistics table.

usdL2fSessionStatusEntry.name: usdL2fSessionStatusEntry
usdL2fSessionStatusEntry.description: An L2F session interface status and statistics entry.

usdL2fSessionStatusIfIndex.name: usdL2fSessionStatusIfIndex
usdL2fSessionStatusIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of an L2F session interface.

usdL2fSessionStatusLocalSessionId.name: usdL2fSessionStatusLocalSessionId
usdL2fSessionStatusLocalSessionId.description: The local session ID for the session.

usdL2fSessionStatusRemoteSessionId.name: usdL2fSessionStatusRemoteSessionId
usdL2fSessionStatusRemoteSessionId.description: The remote session ID for the session.

usdL2fSessionStatusUserName.name: usdL2fSessionStatusUserName
usdL2fSessionStatusUserName.description: The peer session name on this interface, typically the login name of the remote user. If the user name is unknown this object will contain a zero-length string.

usdL2fSessionStatusEffectiveAdminState.name: usdL2fSessionStatusEffectiveAdminState
usdL2fSessionStatusEffectiveAdminState.description: The administrative state currently in effect. This could be the configured admin state for this session, or an overriding admin state exerted from a higher hierarchical level (system, destination, tunnel).

usdL2fSessionStatusState.name: usdL2fSessionStatusState
usdL2fSessionStatusState.description: The current state of the session.

usdL2fSessionStatusCallType.name: usdL2fSessionStatusCallType
usdL2fSessionStatusCallType.description: The type of call and role this tunnel peer is providing for this session. For example, lacIncoming(1) indicates this tunnel peer is acting as a LAC and generated a Incoming-Call-Request to the tunnel peer (the LNS). Note that tunnel peers can be both LAC and LNS simultaneously.

usdL2fSessionStatusTxConnectSpeed.name: usdL2fSessionStatusTxConnectSpeed
usdL2fSessionStatusTxConnectSpeed.description: The last known transmit baud rate for this session.

usdL2fSessionStatusRxConnectSpeed.name: usdL2fSessionStatusRxConnectSpeed
usdL2fSessionStatusRxConnectSpeed.description: The last known receive baud rate for this session.

usdL2fSessionStatusProxyLcp.name: usdL2fSessionStatusProxyLcp
usdL2fSessionStatusProxyLcp.description: Indicates whether the LAC performed proxy LCP for this session.

usdL2fSessionStatusAuthMethod.name: usdL2fSessionStatusAuthMethod
usdL2fSessionStatusAuthMethod.description: The proxy authentication method employed by the LAC for the session. If usdL2fSessionProxyLcp is false(2) this object reports a value of 'none' and should be ignored.

usdL2fSessionStatusSequencingState.name: usdL2fSessionStatusSequencingState
usdL2fSessionStatusSequencingState.description: Indicates which tunnel peers have requested payload sequencing.

usdL2fSessionStatusLacTunneledIfIndex.name: usdL2fSessionStatusLacTunneledIfIndex
usdL2fSessionStatusLacTunneledIfIndex.description: For pass-through remote client sessions (conventional LAC), the ifIndex of an associated local interface through which the remote LAC client was connected. If unknown, this object contains a value of zero. For locally originated sessions (LNS-like), this object has a value of zero.

usdL2fSessionStatusCumEstabTime.name: usdL2fSessionStatusCumEstabTime
usdL2fSessionStatusCumEstabTime.description: The cumulative time in seconds that this session, since first being created, has spent in the established state (which may be punctuated by intervals outside the established state).

usdL2fSessionStatEntry.name: usdL2fSessionStatEntry
usdL2fSessionStatEntry.description: An L2F session interface statistics entry.

usdL2fSessionStatIfIndex.name: usdL2fSessionStatIfIndex
usdL2fSessionStatIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of an L2F session interface.

usdL2fSessionStatPayRecvErrors.name: usdL2fSessionStatPayRecvErrors
usdL2fSessionStatPayRecvErrors.description: Number of payload packets incurring reception errors.

usdL2fSessionStatPayRecvDiscards.name: usdL2fSessionStatPayRecvDiscards
usdL2fSessionStatPayRecvDiscards.description: Number of payload packets discarded after reception.

usdL2fSessionStatPaySendErrors.name: usdL2fSessionStatPaySendErrors
usdL2fSessionStatPaySendErrors.description: Number of payload packets incurring transmission errors.

usdL2fSessionStatPaySendDiscards.name: usdL2fSessionStatPaySendDiscards
usdL2fSessionStatPaySendDiscards.description: Number of payload packets discarded before transmission.

usdL2fSessionStatRecvOutOfSequence.name: usdL2fSessionStatRecvOutOfSequence
usdL2fSessionStatRecvOutOfSequence.description: The number of packets received out of sequence.

usdL2fSessionStatResequencingTimeouts.name: usdL2fSessionStatResequencingTimeouts
usdL2fSessionStatResequencingTimeouts.description: The number of reassembly timeouts that have occurred.

usdL2fSessionStatPayLostPackets.name: usdL2fSessionStatPayLostPackets
usdL2fSessionStatPayLostPackets.description: When sequence numbers are enabled, this value represents the estimated number of payload packets lost, based on observed gaps in sequence numbers. This estimate is subject to correction (decrement) upon receipt of out-of-sequence packets that fill previously observed gaps.

usdL2fUdpIpDestTable.name: usdL2fUdpIpDestTable
usdL2fUdpIpDestTable.description: The L2F UDP/IP destination table. Reports the UDP/IP characteristics of a L2F UDP/IP destination. A L2F UDP/IP destination is associated with a local router, a local IP address, and with a remote IP address for the L2F peer. More specific UDP/IP detail per tunnel is reported in the usdL2fUdpIpTunnelTable.

usdL2fUdpIpDestEntry.name: usdL2fUdpIpDestEntry
usdL2fUdpIpDestEntry.description: Describes the UDP/IP attributes of an L2F destination.

usdL2fUdpIpDestIfIndex.name: usdL2fUdpIpDestIfIndex
usdL2fUdpIpDestIfIndex.description: Same value as ifIndex for the corresponding entry in Interfaces MIB ifTable.

usdL2fUdpIpDestRouterIndex.name: usdL2fUdpIpDestRouterIndex
usdL2fUdpIpDestRouterIndex.description: The index of an entry in the usdRouterTable for the local router with which this L2F destination interface is associated.

usdL2fUdpIpDestLocalAddress.name: usdL2fUdpIpDestLocalAddress
usdL2fUdpIpDestLocalAddress.description: This L2F destination's local IP address.

usdL2fUdpIpDestRemoteAddress.name: usdL2fUdpIpDestRemoteAddress
usdL2fUdpIpDestRemoteAddress.description: The IP address of the remote L2F endpoint.

usdL2fUdpIpTunnelTable.name: usdL2fUdpIpTunnelTable
usdL2fUdpIpTunnelTable.description: The L2F UDP/IP tunnel table. Reports the UDP/IP characteristics of L2F UDP/IP tunnels. A L2F UDP/IP tunnel is defined in terms of the local and remote IP addresses and UDP ports.

usdL2fUdpIpTunnelIfIndex.name: usdL2fUdpIpTunnelIfIndex
usdL2fUdpIpTunnelIfIndex.description: Same as the value of ifIndex for the corresponding entry in Interfaces MIB ifTable.

usdL2fUdpIpTunnelRouterIndex.name: usdL2fUdpIpTunnelRouterIndex
usdL2fUdpIpTunnelRouterIndex.description: The index of an entry in the usdRouterTable for the local router with which this L2F tunnel interface is associated.

usdL2fUdpIpTunnelLocalAddress.name: usdL2fUdpIpTunnelLocalAddress
usdL2fUdpIpTunnelLocalAddress.description: The local IP address for this UDP/IP tunnel.

usdL2fUdpIpTunnelLocalPort.name: usdL2fUdpIpTunnelLocalPort
usdL2fUdpIpTunnelLocalPort.description: The local UDP port for this UDP/IP tunnel.

usdL2fUdpIpTunnelRemoteAddress.name: usdL2fUdpIpTunnelRemoteAddress
usdL2fUdpIpTunnelRemoteAddress.description: The remote IP address for this UDP/IP tunnel.

usdL2fUdpIpTunnelRemotePort.name: usdL2fUdpIpTunnelRemotePort
usdL2fUdpIpTunnelRemotePort.description: The remote UDP port for this UDP/IP tunnel.

usdL2fCompliance.name: usdL2fCompliance
usdL2fCompliance.description: The compliance statement for SNMPv2 entities which implement the L2F MIB.

usdL2fConfigGroup.name: usdL2fConfigGroup
usdL2fConfigGroup.description: A collection of objects providing configuration information of the L2F protocol, tunnels and sessions.

usdL2fStatusGroup.description: A collection of objects providing status of the L2F protocol at the system, destination, tunnel, and session levels.

usdL2fStatGroup.name: usdL2fStatGroup
usdL2fStatGroup.description: A collection of objects providing statistics of the L2F protocol at the destination, tunnel, and session levels.
